In addition to aggression, depression, which is associated with social isolation, both in the elderly and in young people (
 Domènech-Abella et al., 2017; 
 Ge et al., 2017) can alter levels of key cytokines in the inflammatory process. Increased circulating IL-6 has been observed in humans suffering from major depression (
 Maes et al., 1997; 
 Kiecolt-Glaser et al., 2003; 
 Hodes et al., 2014; 
 Kiraly et al., 2017).
